  "prompt": "What are the legal definitions of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of making illegally-obtained money appear legal by passing it through complex financial transactions. Key legal definitions typically include:\n\n1. Basic elements:\n- Concealing the origin of illegally obtained money\n- Transforming criminal proceeds into seemingly legitimate funds\n- Disguising the source of financial assets\n\n2. Common legal components:\n- Intentional financial transactions\n- Knowing the funds originated from criminal activity\n- Attempting to make illegal funds appear legitimate\n\n3. Typical stages:\n- Placement: Introducing illegal funds into financial system\n- Layering: Concealing source through complex transactions\n- Integration: Reintroducing funds as apparently legitimate income\n\n4. Jurisdictional variations exist, but most definitions involve:\n- Criminal intent\n- Financial transactions\n- Attempting to hide illicit fund origins\n\n5. Regulated under:\n- Bank Secrecy Act\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- International financial regulations\n\nPlease note this is general legal information, not specific legal advice. Precise definitions can vary by jurisdiction.",
